  "posts": [
    {
      "id": "2046661738339430489",
      "text": "Does an LLM keep the same judgment when you swap the answer order? New LLM Position Bias Benchmark!\n\nJudge models compare two lightly edited versions of the same story twice, with the order swapped. The median model flips in 45% of decisive case pairs. GPT-5.4 is worst at 66%! https://t.co/Ydgkz1TdIe",
      "conversation_id": "2046661738339430489",
      "entities": {
        "urls": [
          {
            "start": 278,
            "end": 301,
            "url": "https://t.co/Ydgkz1TdIe",
            "expanded_url": "https://x.com/LechMazur/status/2046661738339430489/photo/1",
            "display_url": "pic.x.com/Ydgkz1TdIe",
            "media_key": "3_2046536862773211136"
          }
        ]
      },
      "edit_history_tweet_ids": [
        "2046661738339430489"
      ],
      "created_at": "2026-04-21T18:45:58.000Z",
      "author_id": "35654959"
    },
    {
      "in_reply_to_user_id": "35654959",
      "referenced_tweets": [
        {
          "type": "replied_to",
          "id": "2046661738339430489"
        }
      ],
      "id": "2046661740998586793",
      "text": "As LLMs are used more often as graders and preference labelers, judge reliability matters more. This benchmark isolates one basic and frustrating failure mode.\n\nThe model-average first-shown pick rate is 63%. GPT-5.4 (high) is the most position-sensitive model in the run. https://t.co/t74VKC84vb",
      "conversation_id": "2046661738339430489",
      "entities": {
        "urls": [
          {
            "start": 273,
            "end": 296,
            "url": "https://t.co/t74VKC84vb",
            "expanded_url": "https://x.com/LechMazur/status/2046661740998586793/photo/1",
            "display_url": "pic.x.com/t74VKC84vb",
            "media_key": "3_2046536896289853440"
          }
        ]
      },
      "edit_history_tweet_ids": [
        "2046661740998586793"
      ],
      "created_at": "2026-04-21T18:45:58.000Z",
      "author_id": "35654959"
    },
    {
      "in_reply_to_user_id": "35654959",
      "referenced_tweets": [
        {
          "type": "replied_to",
          "id": "2046661740998586793"
        }
      ],
      "id": "2046661743888486508",
      "text": "Many models don't just pick the first story more often, they also rate it higher. Average first-position rating bonus is +0.26 on a 1-7 scale. Mistral Large 3 is the outlier in the opposite direction. https://t.co/Wj24qyu4rb",
      "conversation_id": "2046661738339430489",
      "entities": {
        "urls": [
          {
            "start": 201,
            "end": 224,
            "url": "https://t.co/Wj24qyu4rb",
            "expanded_url": "https://x.com/LechMazur/status/2046661743888486508/photo/1",
            "display_url": "pic.x.com/Wj24qyu4rb",
            "media_key": "3_2046536980234694656"
          }
        ]
      },
      "edit_history_tweet_ids": [
        "2046661743888486508"
      ],
      "created_at": "2026-04-21T18:45:59.000Z",
      "author_id": "35654959"
    },
    {
      "in_reply_to_user_id": "35654959",
      "referenced_tweets": [
        {
          "type": "replied_to",
          "id": "2046661743888486508"
        }
      ],
      "id": "2046661746635763960",
      "text": "Two failure modes in one chart: directional first-position pull, and order instability even when net first-position lift looks modest. https://t.co/sLkye2c8hO",
      "conversation_id": "2046661738339430489",
      "entities": {
        "urls": [
          {
            "start": 135,
            "end": 158,
            "url": "https://t.co/sLkye2c8hO",
            "expanded_url": "https://x.com/LechMazur/status/2046661746635763960/photo/1",
            "display_url": "pic.x.com/sLkye2c8hO",
            "media_key": "3_2046545938668310528"
          }
        ]
      },
      "edit_history_tweet_ids": [
        "2046661746635763960"
      ],
      "created_at": "2026-04-21T18:46:00.000Z",
      "author_id": "35654959"
    },
    {
      "in_reply_to_user_id": "35654959",
      "referenced_tweets": [
        {
          "type": "replied_to",
          "id": "2046661746635763960"
        }
      ],
      "id": "2046661749425021090",
      "text": "This chart decomposes each model's two-view outcomes into stable picks, position-following flips, and unresolved cases. Xiaomi MiMo V2 Pro has the lowest flip rate (20%) but only 55% coverage. ByteDance Seed2.0 Pro and DeepSeek V3.2 are the cleanest with solid coverage. https://t.co/98CdOGOZ2Z",
      "conversation_id": "2046661738339430489",
      "entities": {
        "urls": [
          {
            "start": 271,
            "end": 294,
            "url": "https://t.co/98CdOGOZ2Z",
            "expanded_url": "https://x.com/LechMazur/status/2046661749425021090/photo/1",
            "display_url": "pic.x.com/98CdOGOZ2Z",
            "media_key": "3_2046537873348825088"
          }
        ]
      },
      "edit_history_tweet_ids": [
        "2046661749425021090"
      ],
      "created_at": "2026-04-21T18:46:00.000Z",
      "author_id": "35654959"
    },
    {
      "in_reply_to_user_id": "35654959",
      "referenced_tweets": [
        {
          "type": "replied_to",
          "id": "2046661749425021090"
        }
      ],
      "id": "2046661752549671122",
      "text": "Worked example: Case 3 \"midnight bakery\". Same pair, opposite orders.\n\nhttps://t.co/MdkgSpGMiV\n\nGPT-5.4 (high) returns &lt;answer&gt;1&lt;/answer&gt; in both prompts. Always the first-shown story, so the underlying winner flips on swap.",
